BEGIN_PGML
For any function [`f: \mathbb{N} \to \mathbb{N}`] and any set [`A \subseteq \mathbb{N}\text{,}`] we can define the image of [`A`] under [`f`] to be the set of all outputs of [`f`] when the input is an element of [`A\text{.}`]  We write this as [`f(A) = \{f(x) ~:~ x \in A\}\text{.}`]

For the following tasks, let's explore the function [`f: \mathbb{N} \to \mathbb{N}`] defined by [`f(x) = x^2 - 3x + 8\text{.}`]

END_PGML

