############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML We will say that two numbers between 1 and 31 are related, written [`a \sim b`] if their difference is a multiple of 7. So for example, [`3 \sim 24\text{,}`] since [`24-3 = 3\cdot 7\text{,}`] but [`3 \not\sim 15`] since [`15-3 = 12`] which is not a multiple of 7.
