solution.p:
Now all the ways to distribute the 15 units to the four y_i variables can be found using stars and bars, specifically 15 stars and 3 bars, so {18 \choose 15} ways. But this includes the ways that one or more y_i variables can be assigned more than 3 units. So subtract using PIE to get

\displaystyle{                {18 \choose 3} -\left( {4\choose 1} {12 \choose 3}-{4\choose 2} {6 \choose 3} + \dots \right)
              }

statement.p:
For each of the following, find the number of shortest lattice paths from (4,4) to (10,10) which: 




pass through the point (6,5)\text{.}






avoid (do not pass through) the point (9,9)\text{.}






either pass through (6,5) or (9,9) (or both).

